potstick
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:[sp. to early wool scouring] a long wooden pole used to stir and lift wool during the scouring process.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
